      "procedureSteps": [
        {
          "stepDescription": "Remove head, tail and upper skin from prawns and wash it thoroughly with salt and 2-3 pinch of turmeric to remove raw smell.",
          "stepImages": []
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Marinate shrimp (prawns) with above ingredients and keep it aside.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_1.JPG",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Pressure cooker is used for this recipe, so I prefer cooking directly into it. If you don't have one, cook in any regular vessel. Heat oil in a pressure cooker. Once heated, put bay leaf, cloves, cardamom. Allow it to sizzle. Add onions and fry until brown. Add  ginger garlic paste, curry leaves and saute for a minute.  Add tomatoes, fry till it starts leaving oil.",
